La Liga champions, Barcelona, have shortlisted four strikers to replace Luis Suarez at the club. Suarez, who is 32 years of age, is in the later stage of his career at Barcelona. The Uruguay international has won lots of trophies at Camp Nou since joining Barcelona from Liverpool in 2014. He has scored over 164 goals in over 220 appearances for Barcelona. According to Mundo Deportivo, Paris Saint-Germain’s Kylian Mbappe is the top target to replace Suarez, while Inter Milan’s Lautaro Martinez props up the list. The other two strikers are; Tottenham Hotspur’s Harry Kane and Manchester United’s Marcus Rashford. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.